  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2021-09-13",
    "date": "2022-09-15T16:00:45Z",
    "text": "Fiscal Analysis by Income and Race Scoring Act or the FAIR Scoring Act\n\nThis bill requires the Congressional Budget Office's (CBO's) cost estimates for legislation to include a distributional analysis by race and income if the legislation will have a gross budgetary effect of at least 0.1% of gross domestic product in any fiscal year during the 10-year budget window.\n\nCBO's analysis must show the transfers that would result by race and income level, and the effects must be shown both in dollars and as a percent change in after-tax-and-transfer-income.\n\nThe bill also requires CBO to report to Congress on methods for conducting such a distributional analysis by gender."
  },
